Class Player

  • java.lang.Object
    • greenfoot.Actor
      • Clickable
        • Player
  • public class Player
extends Clickable
    A player in this simulation, of which there are two. Adjustable properties: - Clicks per second - Number of clickers - Number of starting grandmas "AI" behaviour: - If it has enough cookies to buy the cookie rocket, it shall do so immediately - Default state: choose a random point on the cookie and click there - Every 10-15 clicks, it shall attempt to perform a random action: - Click on a random clickable building - Buy a random building - Buy a random powerup - Buy a random sabotage
    Version:
    November 2022
    Author:
    Eddie Zhuang

              int clickers,
              int cps,
              int grandmas,
              String name,

        Parameters:
        width - The width all the player's stuff will take up (rows, cookie, counter text, etc.)
        height - The width all the player's stuff will take up (rows, cookie, counter text, etc.)
        clickers - How many clickers the player will start off with
        cps - The number of clicks per second each clicker will be able to have
        grandmas - Number of starting grandmas
        name - The name of the player, for text displays. Example: "Player 1"
        isRed - Whether the player is red or not (blue)
